text: I would call this place Pacific Park Unsocial. No one acknowledged me when I came in and then they went on to serve someone who came in after me. So I left.
$11 for a proscuitto panini with one slice of proscuitto...the same for my wife who had a mortadello panini. The ingredients were great almost non-existent. We expected alot more from a $11 sandwich.
I really dig the food here. Panninis are classic, coffee is on point.
